  Translator: Burton Watson
By: Zhuangzi
Locus:
  Chapter: 14
  Paragraph: 26
Title: The Turning Of Heaven
---
Confucius had gone along until he was fifty-one and had still not heard
the Way. Finally he went south to P'ei and called on Lao Tan. "Ah, you
have come," said Lao Tan. "I've heard that you are a worthy man of the
northern region. Have you found the Way?"
